article.description: — Ben Krikke had 28 points in Valparaiso's 81-65 victory over Western Michigan on Sunday night.
article.headline: Valparaiso earns 81-65 win over Western Michigan
article.linkText: Valparaiso earns 81-65 win over Western Michigan
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- — Ben Krikke had 28 points in Valparaiso's 81-65 victory over Western Michigan on Sunday night. Krikke was 13 of 24 shooting, including 0 for 3 from distance, and went 2 for 5 from the line for the Beacons (1-1). Kobe King scored 26 points while shooting 9 for 13 (3 for 4 from 3-point range) and 5 of 5 from the free throw line. Quinton Green added 10 points. The Broncos (1-2) were led by Lamar Norman Jr., who recorded 25 points. Tray Maddox Jr. added 16 points for Western Michigan. In addition, Markeese Hastings finished with six points. Up next for Valparaiso is a Wednesday matchup with Chicago State on the road. Western Michigan visits Houston Baptist on Friday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
